    "narrative": "The outlook for Ghost Ride the WHIP today leans heavily on high-upside speed threats and favorable park factors. **Corbin Carroll** (74.01) stands as our premier play, benefiting from a neutral matchup against Sproat and a premium spot in the three-hole, while **Josh Naylor** (71.58) provides the day\u2019s most reliable floor, bolstered by an 11% boost from his facing Bradley. Despite the focus on SB scarcity, **Brice Turang** (64.04) and **Kyle Karros** (63.06) are essential starts; **Karros** specifically benefits from an elite matchup against the vulnerable Williamson, enjoying a 19% SP skill advantage. We are also monitoring **Trevor Story** (61.48) closely; while Lauer is a tricky arm, the historical BvP edge of 8% across 27 plate appearances makes him a surprisingly sharp play for today\u2019s utility slot.\n\nThe most difficult bench decision involved **Travis Bazzana** (46.08), who narrowly missed the cut behind the superior daily efficiency of **Jose Caballero**. While **Bazzana** offered solid platoon utility, the aggregate projections favored the depth of our middle-of-the-pack starters over his current floor. Risks remain for the bottom of our order, specifically **Jose Caballero** and **Luis Campusano** (44.24), who both face significant headwinds due to batting order placement. We are also navigating caution with **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** (53.30), whose score was dragged down by 19% against Eovaldi\u2019s elite profile. Owners should watch the wind reports closely, as the added air resistance/carry variables are currently providing the small percentage points keeping **Dalton Rushing** (59.00) and **Alex Freeland** (49.99) in the conversation for daily productivity.",
